A ransom of R1 million was then demanded for his release. CAPE TOWN - Three people have been arrested in connection with the kidnapping of a Chinese businessman. It's alleged the businessman was kidnapped in Monte Vista in Cape Town at the weekend. A ransom of R1 million was then demanded for his release. The police's Noloyiso Rwexana said: “The alleged kidnappers settled for R100,000 after negotiations with the family - which was subsequently paid. Shortly after his release, police arrested three suspects aged 31, 33 and 40 in Kraaifontein.” Rwexana says more arrests are imminent.